6. vertice ortus: the Rhine proper is actually formed by the confluence of two tributariesy the ‘ Hinter ’ Rhine and the ‘ Vorder ’ Rhine, which rise in different parts of the Swiss canton Grisons. The source of the Vorder Rhine is near St. Gotthard, ancient Adula, the vernem here referred to.

7. versus: a participle, refiexive in force.

8. molli et clementer edito: cf. our English expression “ a gentle slope’'; there is a contrast with inaccesso ac praecipiti.

9. Abnobae: the name applied in ancient times to the Black Forest. The source of the Danube is on the eastern slope.— pluris: here equivalent to compluris.
